Explanation:
The solution iterates through the string character by character and increments a counter for each non-space character found. Since the problem only requires counting the number of segments, the time complexity is O(n), where n is the length of the string. The space complexity is O(1) because only a single integer variable is used, and no additional space is needed for the problem. The energy implications are low because the algorithm operates efficiently without consuming excessive resources.

